(18, 'en-us', 'Tancredo Neves Campus', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><div style=\"text-align:center;\"><div style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"http://192.168.2.175/assets/files/slide ctan (4) (1).jpg\"></div><br></div></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b><br></b></div><div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-000678b3-7fff-50d2-3ea7-a001290def41\"><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><font face=\"Arial\">The Tancredo Neves<i> Campus</i> is the UFSJ campus with the largest extension, with an area five times bigger than the other campuses combined. This UFSJ facility is located on the margins of the highway BR 494.</font></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><font face=\"Arial\"><br></font></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><font face=\"Arial\">Currently, this campus offers undergraduate courses in Administration, Applied Arts, Architecture and Urban Planning, Accountancy, Computer Science, Economic Sciences, Social Communication (Journalism), Physical Education, Geography, Music, Theatre, and Animal Husbandry.&nbsp;</font></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><font face=\"Arial\"><br></font></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><font face=\"Arial\">Besides having a modern indoor gymnasium and buildings that house several labs, the Music Department building, that has special acoustic treatment, stands out. Attached to this campus is the Risoleta Neves Experimental Farm, run by Epamig, a company linked to the state government, that carries out local agricultural research.&nbsp;</font></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><font face=\"Arial\">&nbsp;</font></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><font face=\"Arial\">Tancredo Neves <i>Campus</i> Address:</font></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-variant-numeric:=\"\" normal;=\"\" font-variant-east-asian:=\"\" vertical-align:=\"\" baseline;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><font face=\"Arial\">Rodovia 494, s/n - Bairro Colônia do Bengo - São João del-Rei</f