(26, 'en-us', 'Planetarium', '<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-8e2ee9b5-7fff-9c5a-43a1-0ea3d4edbcdf\"><div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 12pt;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><div style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"http://192.168.2.175/assets/files/chuvademeteoros (1).jpg\"></div><br></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 12pt;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\">The planetarium, a space of exceptional non-formal education, offers several sessions in the dome that approaches, in an interdisciplinary way, Astronomy and Science contexts, with appropriate languages for a wide age and schooling range of its public.</span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><font face=\"Arial\"><br></font></div><font face=\"Arial\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 12pt;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 12pt;\">The digital planetarium of the Department of Natural sciences (DCNAT- UFSJ), in partnership with LIFE, has last-generation equipments and accessories that allow the development of diversified didactic activities aimed for cultural entertainment, scientific education of the school community, and awakening the students’ interest in the area of exact sciences.</span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-size: 12pt;\"><br></span></div></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 12pt;=\"\" white-space:=\"\" pre-wrap;\"=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: jus