(146, 'en-us', 'History', '<div><div><span style=\"font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Since the implementation of the Sao Joao del Rei Higher Education Foundation (FUNREI) as a Federal Institution in 1987, the History department has been involved in various activities aimed at research and teaching improvement. The History course was created in 2003 and since then has contributed to the training of new generations of professionals, teachers, and researchers. The course is located at the Dom Bosco campus and offers the modalities of Bachelor’s and Licensing in History with classes offered in the evening. We seek, through the interaction between teaching, research, and extension, to ensure the development of skills and abilities that define the profile of individuals with degrees in History. At the end of the course, the person will be able to combine a mastery of the fundamental instruments of the craft, both in the production and dissemination of historical knowledge, with a solid formation and qualification for the exercise of teaching activities.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><o:p></o:p></span></div></div>', 37),
